cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with generating imperative programs from Answer Set Programming Specifications, which involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques such as negation-as-failure. Hence, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with programming languages and software engineering concepts such as synthesis and specifications, which makes cs.PL and cs.SE likely sub-categories. The paper also involves logical reasoning and combinatorial search problems, which makes cs.LO a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves novel ways of synthesizing programs, which makes cs.LG a possible sub-category.
